  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Examining the attitudes of local people toward elephants in a human-elephant conflict in southern Bhutan.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will study the attitudes of local people towards Asian elephants in a high human-elephant conflict (HEC) area of southern Bhutan and will help to understand the types and extent of HEC in this region. Project activities include: 1) questionnaire and survey design, planning, development, and pre-testing of the survey instrument; 2) survey of agriculturalists in the conflict zone; 3) comparison of the number and intensity of HEC events with and without HEC mitigation (electric fences) tools in use; 4) provision of elephant conservation education and awareness programs to youth and farmers in the conflict area. The results from this study will be used to inform land use planners and conservationists to better plan, design, and implement HEC mitigation actions and ultimately conserve Asian elephants in Bhutan.</narrative>
  </description>
